> Szechuan food is like the culinary equivalent of ziplining—its signature aromatic spices are exhilarating and may even give you an adrenaline rush. Our chefs channeled that sensation into a veggie noodle stir-fry that's tossed in a Szechuan-style sauce. Mellowed with peanut butter and sweet soy glaze, the sauce is plentiful enough to coat springy ramen noodles and a bounty of veggies, including mushrooms, broccoli, cauliflower, and carrot. We promise the flavors will take you to new heights.

Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{4%oz} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!). Cut @broccoli, cauliflower, and carrot blend{6%oz} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

In a #small bowl{}, whisk together @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp}, half the @Szechuan paste{2%tbsp}, half the @rice wine vinegar{5%tsp}, half the @peanut butter{1.15%oz}, @sugar{1.5%tsp}, and @water{1/4%cup} until smooth.

> For 4 servings, use all the Szechuan paste, vinegar, and peanut butter, 3 tsp sugar, and 1/3 cup water.

Once water is boiling, add 3/4 of the @ramen noodles{6%oz} to #pot{} (we sent more; save the rest for another use). Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, about ~{1-2%minutes}. Drain and thoroughly rinse under cold water for at least ~{30%seconds}. Toss with a drizzle of oil. (This stops cooking and helps prevent sticky noodles!)

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{4%tsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms; cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, about ~{2-4%minutes}.

Add broccoli, cauliflower, and carrot blend and @water{2%tsp}; cover immediately and let steam for ~{3%minutes}.

Uncover and add a large drizzle of oil. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are tender and lightly browned, about ~{3-5%minutes} more.

Add scallion whites and cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}.

Reduce heat to medium. Add sauce to pan with veggies; cook, stirring, until thickened and slightly reduced, about ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add drained noodles and @butter{1%tbsp}. Toss until noodles are warmed through and thoroughly combined, about ~{1-2%minutes}. (TIP: If needed, stir in water a splash at a time until noodles are coated in sauce.) Season with @?salt{} and @?pepper{} if desired.

Divide stir-fry between bowls. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.